        June 12, 2009<br><br>JMJ / MMM 090611 Thursday<br>Warm Greetings, NightSpirit -- and Everyone --<br>That Name God spoke to Moses, I AM, is so full, theologically and philosophically! I like to think of the burning bush story this way -- Moses is told to go preach and he's scared. Because a false prophet could be stoned to death. Moses asks, &quot;<font color="Blue">Lord, please tell me Your Name. They're gonna ask!</font>&quot; And God says to Moses the equivalent of, &quot;<font color="blue">I AM the One Who alone deserves to be said I Exist. I AM Utter Being. And you, Moses, little man, you are who doesn't exist. You have no name or existence apart from Me. So you tell them <b>I AM</b> Who Exists Necessarily and Absolutely. You go tell them THAT!</font>&quot; They couldn't have understood that, of course. Not at that time.<br>The preposition &quot;in&quot; has fascinated me for years. You quoted <b><font color="Black">John</font></b> 14:20, a further Divine mystery, &quot;<font color="Blue">In that day you will real-ize that I AM in the Father .. and that the Father IS in me .. and that you ARE in me .. and that I AM in you.</font>&quot; That quotation can't be paid proper attention except in a new thread. I have in mind to trigger off some good sharing with a new thread.<br>I also had an experience well over a half century ago -- for one single day -- that never repeated again. But it was a locking into position for me that could never be taken from me. It was a Divine Gift.<br>Blessing in Jesus Christ and in Mary! John</span>
