        <br><span class="subBodyText">
        June 10, 2009<br><br>Your phrasing was good, NightSpirit.  &#8220;<font color="blue">I believe God has revealed the truth in the Bible in encapsulated form and then reveals Himself, His truths, His secrets, further to those who seek Him out.</font>&#8221;  One or two points of polish.  According to the teaching of the Church there are two equally important sources of God&#8217;s Revelation .. Holy Scripture and the Church.  As spiritual children we grasp pretty much the surface of the truth, mostly in human terms we can understand.  As we respond to God with a good heart, the meanings of phrases and sayings comes clear.  And, yes, there are deep things of God that God shares with those who love Him much.  I wouldn&#8217;t call them secrets, though, because God&#8217;s Infinite Generosity wants to share His deepest truths with everyone -- but most are not ready for that.<br><br>Somewhere in the psalms it says, &#8220;<font color="Blue">God Spoke One Word .. I heard two.</font>&#8221;  I see in those words that God, in the Trinity, Spoke eternally the One Word, the Second Person .. Whom He also spoke in Jesus Christ.  God Speaks.  What is it I hear?  Two words?  Many, many words!  Over a lifetime I slowly, by God&#8217;s grace, join these words more and more into &#8220;phrases and clauses and sentences,&#8221; understanding more and more .. and approaching the total understanding in the One Word of God.<br><br>Jesus spoke to many &#8220;levels&#8221; of human beings at one time.  What a task!  And each heard, if he or she were listening, whatever he or she was capable of understanding at the time.<br><br>Regarding the first two chapters of <b>Genesis</b> &gt;&gt;&gt; The word &#8220;myth&#8221; can be used as a very powerful word, meaning the expression in story form of truths grasped, perhaps partially, by people who, because of the time in which they lived and the culture into which they were born, could absolutely not have grasped such truths in their purity, in their full meaning.  Such are the two different stories of Creation in <b>Genesis</b> 1 and 2.  Try explaining Einsten&#8217;s General Relativity to the six-year old living next door.<br><br>Those instances in which God is said &#8220;to have changed His Mind&#8221; &gt;&gt;&gt; From the first instant of Creation God Knew with certainty that He would &#8220;change&#8221; His Mind.  Actually it&#8217;s no change but simply the continuing fulfillment of what God has in control from the beginning.<br><br>And many times God makes <i>conditional</i> promises being dependent on a people&#8217;s continuing to cooperate with Him.  And these conditional promises are not always explicitly said to be conditional.<br><br>NightSpirit, it&#8217;s always enjoyable to share with you.  Keep worshipping, thanking, loving, repenting, and asking, in the Name of Jesus, for all your needs -- and, yes, for your wants.  Not all will be granted .. but God delights to see His children delight in truly good things.           John</span>
