        <span class="author" style="text-align:left;"><strong>by: Ned</strong></span><br>
        <br><span class="subBodyText">
        June 9, 2009<br><br><blockquote><div>Originally Posted by JohnJFarren</div><br><br>JMJ / MMM     090608<br>Greetings, Ned .. and Everybody --<br>Because the Trinity is a mystery of our faith, that doesn’t mean we can know nothing about it.  There is a good bit we can and do know.<br>To separate the Christ from Jesus .. as you say you do .. is a mistaken approach.  Let us suppose &gt; I come upon you unexpectedly and I give your right hand a mighty whack!  You react instantaneously with, “Why did you <i>hit</i> me!”  <font size="1">(You might have reacted with, “Why did you hit my hand!”  But I doubt it.)</font>  Let’s stick with, “Why did you hit me!”  If I said that I didn’t hit <i>you</i>, I hit your <i>hand</i> .. my separating you from your hand would puzzle you a little.  As far as you’re concerned I did hit <i>you</i>.<br>In Jesus Christ there are not two persons.  There are two natures, the Divine Nature and a human nature, both possessed by the same One Person, the Second of the Trinity.  The human nature of Christ is possessed by, belongs to, the Second Divine Person in the same way your human nature is possessed by, belongs to, <i>you</i>, the one <i>person you</i>.<br>When one grasps strongly what this means, it truly takes an act of faith to believe it!</blockquote><br><br>I didn't mean by the above statement that there was one person Jesus and another person Christ. My apologies for not being clear.<br><br>To give an example of what I do mean, there is a man named Barrack Obama. He is a lot like other men. Similar set up. Yet the label <i>President </i>Barrack Obama adds an aspect to the personality of who this man is. It presents certain powers and a position of leadership. Even when Barrack is playing Candyland with his kids, he is still the Chief Executive Officer of the United States. His kids call him &quot;Daddy&quot; and his co-workers call him &quot;Mr. President&quot;, in either case the label does not diminish the actual personality behind the name. We are just referring to different aspects of the same man.<br><br>Similarly, many people  think of Jesus as a great man, a prophet, a teacher, a revolutionary, a healer, and so on. But to know him as Christ opens an entirely different aspect of Jesus' personality. As Christ Jesus, he is the eternal and only begotten Son of God; the way, the truth, the life. Now the teachings, words and actions of this simple carpenter that lived 2000 years ago have cosmic ramifications. And I agree with you, you can't really understand that without faith.</span>
