        June 8, 2009<br><br>OK, here's what I've come to.<br><br>We know that God is immutable. If anyone disagrees I can post some verses, but I think it is pretty well-known.<br><br>God has a nature. That nature includes love, mercy, justice, and so forth. This nature does not change. God is never not loving, not merciful, or not just (apologies for the double negatives).<br><br>God, however, cannot have emotion because that would require him to be in a temporary state. God is outside of time, so he cannot change.<br><br>Jesus could display emotion because he also has a human nature. Not to mention he was within time when he was on earth.<br><br>That's just how I understand it. I'm interested what others think, though.</span>
