        June 7, 2009<br><br>I could probably reflect on the meaning of the Trinity for the rest of my life and not know all the in's and out's of its significance.<br><br>When it comes to the suffering of Jesus and Jesus being God, I separate the Christ from Jesus to eliminate confusion (not as proper theology). <br><br>Christ is God in man. Jesus is man in God. Jesus Christ is the means through which man and God commune. It is through him that we are no longer separated from God and it is through him that God is no longer separated from us. <br><br>Without Christ, God is beyond our personal grasp. He is an enigma, an omnipresent, omnipotent Being that we can not see or know except through the impersonal observation of creation (his Spirit). And even in that observation, all we have is theory and speculation. We are surrounded by doubt. <br><br>Jesus makes God personal. There is an action required to know God on a personal level, which is faith in Christ's death and resurrection. Through that faith, the reality of the Father becomes clear.</span>
